Rating: 4
Exceptional, even with the caved-in middle (due to the flawed homemade baking powder). But the (very) sweet cake (especially the sugar top) and the tart rhubarb make an exceptional combination. There was no time to attempt the buttermilk ice cream, so I stirred a Tbs of sugar into an 8-oz cup of creme fraiche and drizzled that over the top. Putting it in the freezer for 15 minutes prior to serving might work also. The added sugar made it a bit sweet, but not overpoweringly so, and it made a nice buffer between the tart compote and the super-sweet cake. Definitely a keeper, and a nice change from strawberry/rhubarb.

Rating: 4
I made the cake and it is very, very good in both taste and texture. It also froze very well. The compote is delicious as well and I added other berries to the mix and served with vanilla ice cream.

Rating: 4
I needed an easy cake for a last minute dessert to bring to a dinner party at my parents'. So I cheated and served it with fresh cut strawberries and vanilla icecream. And it was still delicious. The perfect amount of orange flavor in the cake and was a great texture to accompany the berries and icecream. The fam loved it and will definately make it again.

