Rating: 4
I only made the cake from this recipe. I topped it with fresh raspberries (almost a version of the rhubarb compote) and a white wine syrup. The cake really didn't need the topping as it was wonderful on its own but the raspberries in white wine syrup pushed it over the edge. Unbelievably good! I will definitely be making the cake again.

Rating: 4
I made the cake and the ice cream - I couldn't find fresh rhubarb. I substituted a rhubarb/reaspberry perserves I found at my local grocery store. I made the cake and ice cream exactly as the recipe is written. This is a great recipe for people that like desserts taht are not overly sweet. The buttermilk ice cream is really exceptional - I am trying to think of other things I can serve with it.

Rating: 4
I made only the cornmeal cake. I omitted the sugar topping. The cake was simple to make and the sour cream made the cake have tenderness. The butter flavor also came through. We all enjoyed this easy and simple cake.